The article discusses the concerns over the violent crackdown on peaceful protestors in Iran, particularly students and women who are demanding their equal rights and basic human dignity. The United States expresses support for Iranian women and citizens who are inspiring the world with their bravery. The US is taking steps to make it easier for Iranians to access the Internet and is holding accountable Iranian officials and entities responsible for employing violence to suppress civil society. The US plans to impose further costs on perpetrators of violence against peaceful protestors and will continue to support the rights of Iranians to protest freely.